Assuming something like that just doesn&#039;t work.  I don&#039;t do quite as much as you do as far as a count of SQL Saturdays but do enough to know, if I have something like that (vendor or not) that it is far easier and just curtious to say, &quot;Hey, my flight leaves at 5PM so a earlier slot would be AWESOME!&quot;  Aside from that, the schedule was published ahead and changes could have been made after a quick review.  I had one speaker ask for a different time slot and gladly worked to change it for them.  &lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
In fact I just did this for Pensacola and now it is all set, no questions and the organizers can schedule knowing there is a early out person.  And the reason is exactly the same as you gave but I let them know.  &lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
It&#039;s always important to take five minutes to just let the organizers know before mistakes are made (which really, to them it isn&#039;t a msitake with the missing knowledge).  &lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
That&#039;s me responding as a speaker, not an organizer :)

I think that scattering vendor sessions throughout the day was a miss.  &lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
